cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.IR, cs.NE 

This paper deals with natural language processing and specifically focuses on prepositions, which are a crucial part of syntax and semantics in sentences. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also uses tensor decomposition, which is a common technique in machine learning and falls under cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also uses word embeddings, which is a common technique in natural language processing and falls under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also deals with preposition selection and disambiguation, which are common tasks in information retrieval and fall under cs.IR (Information Retrieval). Finally, the paper uses preposition embeddings to achieve better results in downstream tasks, which is a common technique in neural networks and falls under cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
